[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][size=3]Adds on-screen Min and Max buttons next to the craft window's quantity arrows, so you can queue as many as your materials allow (or drop back to one) in a single click.[/size]
[*][size=3]Adds a Max button to the vendor item-count window that fills the slider with as much as you can afford (or as much as the trader has).[/size]
[*][size=3]Controller users can use the Left and Right triggers to snap the craft quantity or vendor amount to minimum/maximum.[/size]
[/list]
[size=4][b]Notes[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][size=3]Large values will cause the game to appear to hang. This is the game, not the mod.[/size]
[*][size=3]Min and Max buttons are hidden on the expanded view of star-quality recipes (the one that lets you pick individual ingredient tiers). That view is built for single, deliberate crafts — collapse it first if you want to batch.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Other mods of mine you might like[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/57]Queue Everything[/url] — queueable crafts across almost every bench, with live totals that update as you change the quantity. MaxButtonsRedux and QueueEverything are the classic pair for mass-crafting.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/62]Where's Ma' Storage[/url] — shared inventory across workstations. You'll want this if you're pressing Max regularly, since the button fills against your combined stock.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/65]FasterCraft Reloaded[/url] — speed up crafting. Pairs with Max to finish batches quickly.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/67]Economy Reloaded[/url] — stable vendor prices so pressing Max at a vendor doesn't get expensive from inflation.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Configuration[/b][/size]

[size=3]If you installed the required [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack[/url] and this mod is configurable, press F1 in-game to open the config interface.[/size]

[size=4][b]Requirements[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79][size=3]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack at Graveyard Keeper Nexus - Mods and community (nexusmods.com)[/size][/url]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/125][size=3]Rest In Patches[/size][/url] — required. Without it installed this mod will refuse to load.
[/list]
[size=4][b]Installation[/b][/size]

[size=3]Installation using Vortex is the recommended installation method. If you wish to install manually, extract the contents of the mod archive into:

[code]...&#92;steamapps&#92;common&#92;Graveyard Keeper&#92;BepInEx[/code][/size]

